<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 09 at 1:32PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow showers will impact portions of
southeastern Madison and southeastern Beaverhead Counties through
245 PM MST...
At 130 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking moderate to heavy snow
showers along a line extending from 24 miles southeast of Virginia
City to 9 miles south of Lima. Movement was east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Moderate to heavy snow showers, winds in excess of 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Reduced visibility down to a half mile or less and slippery
roads.
Locations impacted include...
Virginia City, Ennis, Lima, Monida, Dell, Bannack Pass, Mcallister,
Jeffers, Cameron, and Snowline.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>Slow Down! Rapid changes in visibility and road conditions are
expected.</instruction>
